# ROAR Engine — Cursor Rules

## Project Identity
You are building ROAR Engine — a supervised agentic pipeline for retail dispute resolution.
Stack: Next.js 14 (App Router) · FastAPI (Python) · n8n + LangChain · GPT-4o-mini · PostgreSQL on Railway · Vercel AI SDK · Tailwind CSS.

## Source of Truth
All specs are in /docs. Read the relevant document before writing any code.
Documents override assumptions. Always check schema, API shapes, and component names from docs.

## Repository Structure
roar-engine/
+-- web/     Next.js 14 frontend
+-- api/     FastAPI backend
+-- n8n/     n8n workflow JSON exports
+-- db/      SQL migrations and seed scripts
+-- docs/    All 8 markdown spec documents

## Key Rules
- Next.js 14 App Router ONLY — no pages/ directory
- ALL colors via CSS custom properties — never hardcode hex
- Dark mode via .dark class on html element
- Polling for live chat: GET /cases/:id/messages every 4000ms
- FastAPI async throughout — no sync def for DB operations
- SQLAlchemy async ORM + asyncpg — no Supabase client
- FastAPI JWT auth (python-jose + passlib) — no external auth service
- n8n calls FastAPI /internal/sources/* — never queries DB directly
- chat_messages is append-only — no DELETE or UPDATE
- REFUND_AUTO_THRESHOLD = 500 (THB)
- RETURN_WINDOW_DAYS = 7
- DELIVERY_SLA_BREACH_DAYS = 3
- INACTIVITY_TIMEOUT_MINUTES = 15
- MIN_REJECTION_REASON_CHARS = 50
- CHAT_POLL_INTERVAL_MS = 4000

## Do NOT
- Use Supabase client or Supabase Auth
- Use WebSockets for chat
- Use pages/ directory
- Hardcode colors or business rule values
- Allow n8n direct DB access
- Make chat_messages deletable
- Implement settings screen or analytics dashboard
